          "label": "<p>Between which two muscle layers of the intercostal space does the neurovascular </p>",
          "x": 30,
          "y": 30,
          "width": 40,
          "height": 25,
          "libraryTitle": "Multiple Choice",
          "action": {
            "library": "H5P.MultiChoice 1.16",
            "params": {
              "question": "<p>Between which two muscle layers of the intercostal space does the neurovascular bundle (vein, artery, and nerve) run?</p>",
              "answers": [
                {
                  "text": "<div>External intercostal and internal intercostal</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The neurovascular bundle does not lie between the external and internal intercostal layers. It runs deeper, between the internal and innermost layers.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Internal intercostal and innermost intercostal</div>",
                  "correct": true,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>Correct. The intercostal vessels and nerve run between the internal and innermost intercostal muscles, within the costal groove along the inferior border of each rib.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>External intercostal and innermost intercostal</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The external and innermost layers are not adjacent — the internal intercostal layer lies between them.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                },
                {
                  "text": "<div>Innermost intercostal and endothoracic fascia</div>",
                  "correct": false,
                  "tipsAndFeedback": {
                    "tip": "",
                    "chosenFeedback": "<div>The endothoracic fascia lines the thoracic cavity deep to the innermost intercostal, but the neurovascular bundle lies more superficially, between the internal and innermost layers.</div>",
                    "notChosenFeedback": ""
                  }
                }
              ],
              "overallFeedback": [
                {
                  "from": 0,
                  "to": 50,
                  "feedback": "The neurovascular bundle lies between the internal and innermost intercostal muscles. Remember the three layers from superficial to deep: external → internal → innermost, with the bundle between the last two."
                },
                {
                  "from": 51,
                  "to": 100,
                  "feedback": "Well done. This anatomical relationship is clinically vital — chest drain insertion targets the space just above the lower rib to avoid the VAN bundle tucked into the costal groove above."
                }
              ],
              "behaviour": {
